    "assumptions": [
      "Sensitivity is the range of response across the 2D pressure grid (own level x opponent level), reported as three separate metrics: direction delta (win rate change), conviction delta (avg strength change among picks), and netScore delta (existing 2:1 weighted formula combined view).",
      "Minimum N per cell is 3; cells below threshold are hidden or greyed.",
      "Layout is one model at a time; users switch via a model selector. No side-by-side comparison view in v1.",
      "Lives at a new top-level page under the Models nav link.",
      "Reuses getLevelNormalizationMap from cloud/apps/api/src/graphql/queries/scenarios-utils.ts. Skips options[] alternative phrasing handling because production data does not use it (verified via two definition samples and LevelPresetVersion schema).",
      "Reuses existing strongly/somewhat/neutral decision strength buckets and the canonical netScore formula from canonicalConditionSummary.ts.",
      "Ceiling/floor cases flagged based on baseline win rate at lowest pressure level; not excluded from the report.",
      "New aggregation pivot: across vignettes for the same value pair, indexed by pressure level scores 1-5 on both own and opponent dimensions."
    ],
    "summary": "Discovery complete via pre-skill conversation. User answered all key decisions; carrying assumptions in.",
    "updated_at": 1777326740,
    "answers": {},
    "non_goals": [
      "Statistical machinery: confidence intervals, variance decomposition, multiple-comparison correction, formal hypothesis testing.",
      "Level label recalibration across vignettes (acknowledged as a measurement limitation).",
      "Sycophancy or instruction-following confound detection (acknowledged as a known caveat in limitations panel).",
      "options[] alternative phrasing handling on DimensionLevel (unused in production data).",
      "Curve fitting, slope regression, or any analysis that assumes monotonic response to pressure.",
      "Multi-model side-by-side comparison view (deferred)."
    ],
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "User navigates to a new Pressure Sensitivity page via the Models nav link.",
      "Cross-model summary at top of page ranks models by aggregate sensitivity with inline per-value spread visible.",
      "Per-model detail view shows a table with one row per value pair, columns for direction delta, conviction delta, netScore delta, baseline win rate, and a ceiling/floor flag.",
      "Per-model detail includes a 2D pressure heat map (own level x opponent level) per value pair.",
      "Cells with N < 3 transcripts are hidden or visually distinguished as low-data.",
      "Cross-value heat map (model x value) at page level lets the reader visually answer whether sensitivity is a model trait or value-specific.",
      "Directional sanity check panel at bottom of page reports the percentage of (model, value) pairs where increased own pressure produced increased win rate.",
      "Static limitations panel documents calibration, sycophancy, conviction self-report, and N-gating caveats."
    ],
